then you ain't no better than your wife.

1379
01:25:26.589 --> 01:25:29.185
So get yourself together. man.

1380
01:25:29.186 --> 01:25:32.519
Do the right thing but not for yourself.

1381
01:25:33.816 --> 01:25:34.899
for your son.

1382
01:25:36.493 --> 01:25:37.743
He deserves it.

1383
01:25:56.263 --> 01:25:59.967
- Hey. you mind if I play some music?

1384
01:25:59.968 --> 01:26:01.051
- Yeah. sure.

1385
01:26:05.674 --> 01:26:08.257
(upbeat music)

1386
01:26:15.570 --> 01:26:16.809
- You seems like this one.

1387
01:26:16.810 --> 01:26:17.876
- Oh yeah. yeah.

1388
01:26:17.877 --> 01:26:20.960
I'd say it's an old one from the 90s.

1389
01:26:22.650 --> 01:26:24.817
That was famous back then.

1390
01:26:28.410 --> 01:26:31.156
- I knew the guy who sang it.

1391
01:26:31.157 --> 01:26:31.990
- Really?

1392
01:26:33.237 --> 01:26:34.237
What was it?

1393
01:26:35.730 --> 01:26:38.370
Hollenburg. or Holkenborg?

1394
01:26:39.570 --> 01:26:43.306
Had a couple of hits back in the day.

1395
01:26:43.307 --> 01:26:46.608
Don't know what ever
happened to him after that.

1396
01:26:46.609 --> 01:26:47.942
He disappeared.

1397
01:26:49.263 --> 01:26:51.680
- So who's your favorite now?

1398
01:26:53.610 --> 01:26:56.916
- I don't have any in this decade.

1399
01:26:56.917 --> 01:26:58.917
- Really? May I ask why?

1400
01:27:01.507 --> 01:27:06.142
- Artists back in those
days. had a story to tell.

1401
01:27:06.143 --> 01:27:08.169
an actual art. (laughs)

1402
01:27:08.170 --> 01:27:11.662
And they had to actually be good.

1403
01:27:11.663 --> 01:27:14.663
Not like these hashtag artists in LA

1404
01:27:16.530 --> 01:27:19.353
with their reboots. and their remakes.

1405
01:27:19.354 --> 01:27:21.130
I don't know

1406
01:27:22.596 --> 01:27:25.663
They plug the aux into their iPhones

1407
01:27:27.383 --> 01:27:29.209
Play a song.

1408
01:27:29.210 --> 01:27:31.627
That they sang for the 100th time.

1409
01:27:33.149 --> 01:27:35.329
and then ask my honest opinion.

1410
01:27:35.330 --> 01:27:39.527
(laughs)

1411
01:27:39.528 --> 01:27:44.147
As if they're gonna get
a record deal from me.

1412
01:27:44.148 --> 01:27:47.156
Yeah.

1413
01:27:47.157 --> 01:27:49.407
- Had a story to tell. huh?

1414
01:27:53.063 --> 01:27:55.102
Hey. you know what? Can
you let me out right here?

1415
01:27:55.103 --> 01:27:56.169
- Right here? Are you sure?

1416
01:27:56.170 --> 01:27:58.420
- Yeah. yeah. this is good.

1417
01:28:04.903 --> 01:28:05.736
Thanks.

1418
01:28:20.703 --> 01:28:21.870
Hey. everyone.

1419
01:28:23.250 --> 01:28:25.167
Arthur Holzenberg here.

1420
01:28:26.527 --> 01:28:31.511
and I have a confession that
I wanna get off my chest.

1421
01:28:35.217 --> 01:28:38.378
So. many of you know.
we just had some success

1422
01:28:38.379 --> 01:28:40.629
with the album Nightingale.

1423
01:28:42.219 --> 01:28:43.052
but...

1424
01:28:45.952 --> 01:28:48.911
I didn't write Nightingale.

1425
01:28:48.912 --> 01:28:51.086
It's not even me singing.

1426
01:28:53.194 --> 01:28:54.194
It's my dad.

1427
01:28:55.486 --> 01:28:56.736
It's his songs.

1428
01:28:57.699 --> 01:28:58.949
It's his voice.

1429
01:29:00.524 --> 01:29:03.774
I did it to pay for his medical bills.

1430
01:29:06.473 --> 01:29:07.306
But...

1431
01:29:11.125 --> 01:29:12.289
no excuses.

1432
01:29:12.290 --> 01:29:15.540
At the time it seemed like a good idea.

1433
01:29:19.727 --> 01:29:21.394
- Okay. hello? Yeah.

1434
01:29:23.424 --> 01:29:26.777
I don't know. why'd he do that?

1435
01:29:26.778 --> 01:29:29.566
I... (exhales)

1436
01:29:29.567 --> 01:29:30.417
Well. I don't know.

1437
01:29:30.418 --> 01:29:32.168
I wasn't there. Okay?

1438
01:29:35.040 --> 01:29:36.779
- This is my decision.

1439
01:29:36.780 --> 01:29:40.447
and I have to live with
the consequences. so

1440
01:29:45.000 --> 01:29:48.667
I just thought it was
time to tell my story.

1441
01:29:50.380 --> 01:29:52.130
Thanks for listening.

1442
01:30:05.593 --> 01:30:07.760
(exhales)

1443
01:30:55.356 --> 01:30:58.106
- So what made you do it. Arthur?

1444
01:31:02.556 --> 01:31:04.806
(laughing)

1445
01:31:10.463 --> 01:31:11.296
Oh. well.

1446
01:31:15.062 --> 01:31:17.145
(laughs)

1447
01:31:26.123 --> 01:31:26.955
- No. no. no. no. no.

1448
01:31:26.956 --> 01:31:29.429
Don't mess up your stitches.

1449
01:31:29.430 --> 01:31:31.551
How you feeling?

1450
01:31:31.552 --> 01:31:33.219
- Never felt better.

1451
01:31:34.790 --> 01:31:36.873
(laughs)

1452
01:31:38.135 --> 01:31:41.302
You knew what would happen. didn't ya?

1453
01:31:42.695 --> 01:31:45.628
- Yeah. I did what I wanted.

1454
01:31:45.629 --> 01:31:47.796
- Just to show me you can?

1455
01:31:49.095 --> 01:31:52.669
- Just. it felt better to tell my story

1456
01:31:52.670 --> 01:31:55.589
than to live behind a lie.

1457
01:31:55.590 --> 01:31:57.173
- And you did well.

1458
01:31:58.444 --> 01:32:00.444
You did real well. Art.

1459
01:32:02.110 --> 01:32:06.352
I dunno if I would have
been man enough to do that.

1460
01:32:08.175 --> 01:32:11.053
I am really proud to be your old man.

1461
